# Command d2

## What does this command do:

D2 is a modern diagram scripting language that turns text to diagrams.

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `curl -fsSL https://d2lang.com/install.sh | sh`
For Raspberry Pi install using: `curl -fsSL https://d2lang.com/install.sh | sh`
For Mac install using: `curl -fsSL https://d2lang.com/install.sh | sh`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `~/.local/bin/d2`
For Raspberry Pi run: `~/.local/bin/d2`
For Mac run: `~/.local/bin/d2`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/terrastruct/d2

## Command options

# Compile and render a .d2 file to SVG (default output format):
d2 file.d2

# Render to a specific output format:
d2 file.d2 output.png
d2 file.d2 output.pdf
d2 file.d2 output.gif

# Watch for changes and live reload:
d2 --watch file.d2

# Use a specific layout engine (dagre, elk, tala):
d2 --layout=elk file.d2

# Use a specific theme (run `d2 themes` to list):
d2 --theme=200 file.d2

# Render in sketch/hand-drawn style:
d2 --sketch file.d2

# Set dark mode theme:
d2 --dark-theme=200 file.d2

# Scale the output (0.5 = half size):
d2 --scale=0.5 file.d2 output.png

# Center the diagram in the viewbox:
d2 --center file.d2

# Set pixels of padding around the diagram:
d2 --pad=50 file.d2

# Read from stdin / write to stdout:
echo 'x -> y' | d2 - -
d2 input.d2 --stdout-format png - > output.png

# Animate multiple boards (SVG only, interval in ms):
d2 --animate-interval=1000 file.d2

# Target a specific board to render:
d2 --target='layers.x.*' file.d2

# Bundle all assets into SVG output:
d2 --bundle file.d2

# Force an appendix on SVG exports (for tooltips/links):
d2 --force-appendix file.d2

# Omit XML tag from SVG (useful for HTML embedding):
d2 --no-xml-tag file.d2

# Add a salt for unique IDs (multiple diagrams in same HTML):
d2 --salt=mysalt file.d2

# Set timeout in seconds for large diagrams:
d2 --timeout=300 file.d2

# Use ASCII rendering mode (standard or extended):
d2 --ascii-mode=standard file.d2 output.txt

# Use a custom font:
d2 --font-regular=/path/to/font.ttf file.d2

# Format a .d2 file in place:
d2 fmt file.d2

# Check if a file is correctly formatted:
d2 --check file.d2

# Validate a .d2 file:
d2 validate file.d2

# Open a file in the online playground:
d2 play file.d2

# List available layout engines:
d2 layout

# Show help for a specific layout engine:
d2 layout elk

# List available themes:
d2 themes

# Show version:
d2 --version
